| 361 | FLEX FIELD 20 | STRING | STRING |  | Flexible field set aside future SAM Data elements | Optional | Public |
|  | FLEX FIELD 21 | STRING | STRING | 1 | Flexible field set aside future SAM Data elements | Optional | Public |
|  | FLEX FIELD 22 | STRING | STRING | 2 | Flexible field set aside future SAM Data elements | Optional | Public |
|  | FLEX FIELD 23 | STRING | STRING | 3 | Flexible field set aside future SAM Data elements | Optional | Public |
|  | FLEX FIELD 24 | STRING | STRING | 4 | Flexible field set aside future SAM Data elements | Optional | Public |
| 362 | END OF RECORD INDICATOR | STRING | STRING | 4 | Identifier that serves to demarcate the end of each individual record in the extract file. | Mandatory | Public |

## STRING Clarification

### SAM Numerics Code String

SAM Numerics are various SAM values with a 2-position numeric identification code, followed by up to 4 sequence values.

Format: `~CODE_TYPE^SEQ1_VALUE^SEQ2_VALUE^SEQ3_VALUE^SEQ4_VALUE~`

Example: `~BL^30000000^15000000^30000000^15000000~LS^42^5000000^0^0~PG^1^0^0^0~`

**LS — Local Size**

- Sequence 1: Local Avg. Number of Employees (max 999,999,999,999,999)
- Sequence 2: Local Avg. Annual Revenue (max 999,999,999,999,999)

**BK — SBA NAICS Banking Size**

- Sequence 1: Total Assets from 4th qtr, preceding year

**PG — SBA NAICS Power Generation**

- Sequence 1: Total MWH, preceding fiscal year, all affiliates

**PT — SBA NAICS Petroleum**

- Sequence 1: Bbl/day, Oper. Atmos. Crude Oil Distil. capacity

**BL — Bonding Levels (Disaster Relief)**

- Sequence 1: Construction Bonding Level, Per Contract (dollars)
- Sequence 2: Construction Bonding Level, Aggregate (dollars)
- Sequence 3: Service Bonding Level, Per Contract (dollars)
- Sequence 4: Service Bonding Level, Aggregate (dollars)

### SAM Disaster Response String

Format: `~TYPE_CODE + AREA_CODE~` (tilde-delimited, repeating)

Example: `CTYFL051~CTYFL085~MSA2700~STAFL`

| Type Code | Description |
| --- | --- |
| ANY | Any area |
| STA | State (2-position area code) |
| CTY | County (5-position area code) |
| MSA | Metropolitan Service Area (4-position area code) |

